('2397', '266', 'description', '<h3>Characteristics</h3>\r\nThese valves can either be supplied in trunnion mounted or floating ball execution, side entry, top entry, soft or metal seated as well as sub-sea designs.\r\n\r\nWe can supply these valves with manual levers, gear operators or electric, pneumatic or hydraulic actuator.\r\n\r\nDesign according to API 6D, ASME B16.34\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>side entry and top entry construction</li>\r\n 	<li>full and reduced bore</li>\r\n 	<li>metal to metal and soft seal</li>\r\n 	<li>anti blow out stem</li>\r\n 	<li>double block and bleed</li>\r\n 	<li>single or double piston effect seats</li>\r\n 	<li>fire safe tested api 6fa, api 607, iso 10497</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Materials</h3>\r\nSITINDUSTRIE VALVOmetal utilises several type of material, all complying to ASTM &amp; ASME standards and in accordance to customer needs and specifications (NACE standard included).\r\n\r\nHere below we indicate a list and the main cast and forged materials utilised:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Body</strong>\r\nForged carbon steel, stainless steel, special alloy steel, exotic alloys.Â All cast steel materials for âtop entryâ type.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Trim</strong>\r\nForged or pressed carbon steel, stainless steel, alloy steel, exotic alloys.</li>\r\n</ul>'),
